agus.gunit.execution.assist

Class SURFACE_TO_SPACE_ATMO

  • java.lang.Object
    • agus.gunit.execution.assist.SURFACE_TO_SPACE_ATMO
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ASSIST

    public class SURFACE_TO_SPACE_ATMO
extends java.lang.Object
implements ASSIST
    Will guide a rocket through the atmosphere into an suborbital trajectory with the apoapsis at the height of the parking orbit. Can also be used for non atmosp

    WARNING: This is only a simple test method. Do not expect an perfect ascend

    Author:
    Niklas Heidenreich

      • SurfaceToSpace

        private void SurfaceToSpace(float inclination)
                     throws java.lang.InterruptedException,
                            AGuSDataException
        Guides to Vessel from the surface of a body to space, where space is the parking orbit for that body.

        It will end when the apoapsis exceeds this height.

        This orbit will be suborbital.

        Parameters:
        minThrottlePercent - the minimum throttle the engines should run at
        inclination - the inclination in which to start
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException
        AGuSDataException
